posts.raw_content:
Them: The U.S. didn’t build itself—it grew thanks to immigrant labor, particularly Latino immigrants who have always done the hard work others didn’t want to do

Me: 
You are so wrong it's sad. Latinos didnt do anything but permit themselves to be low wage slaves.  They didnt build jack until the 80's, at which point they started displacing American workers in the southwest and it wasn't any great achievement. it was factories, housing, lettuce, avocados etc.
Go away and build your own nation and make it great. Lewis and Clark weren't Latino, nor were the founding fathers. Latinos didn't participate in whaling or the fur trade, they didn't travel the Oregon trail or tame the west nor Alaska . They didn't win the Pacific or participate in the Gold Rush. They didnt build the Empire state building, the Hoover or Grand Coolee dams, the Golden Gate bridge or the National Parks. They didn't spill blood in a war until the Persian Gulf and we beat their ass in the Mexican American war. We own the Alamo and the southwest including California. Latinos didn't go to the moon, invent the space shuttle, airplane, radio, telephone, steamship, bicycle or electricity, create the cotton gin or the automobile or motorcycle. I WILL NOT allow you to belittle the sacrifices, blood sweat and tears of people that tamed and built America and led innovations of the modern world while Latinos were taking siestas through just about everything above, milling corn and killing each other.
